title: #mentallyhealthy ‚Ä¢ 8 Signs You‚Äôre an Introvert ‚Ä¢ for keeping Mental Health & Wellness ‚Ä¢
description:
Join this channel to get access to perks:
https://bit.ly/MH_CLUB

Staying MentallyHealthy is important - Here are 8 Signs You‚Äôre an Introvert to help keep your Mental Health and Wellness. 

When you hear the word introvert, you most likely think of someone who is shy or quiet and prefers to be alone. As a matter of fact, the American Psychological Association defines introversion as an orientation toward the internal private world of one‚Äôs self and one‚Äôs inner thoughts and feelings, rather than toward the outer world of people and things. However, there is much more to know about this sometimes-misunderstood personality type. 
 
The term introversion was popularized by the 20th century Swiss psychiatrist, Carl Jung, who researched and defined human personality types. In today‚Äôs world, approximately one-third to one-half of the U.S. population are defined as introverts. While most people need occasional solitude, in order to replenish their energy, many introverts have more definitive patterns of behavior. These may include, feeling depleted of energy from being in social situations, taking extra time to make decisions, gaining energy from self-reflection and much more. If you are wondering if you are an introvert, please join us as we explore 8 Signs That You‚Äôre an Introvert.
 
One way to find out if you're an introvert is to take a test, such as the Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI). Watch for our video related to this test, exploring and explaining the 16 different personality types. 

As always, we at Mentally Healthy truly care about your mental health and well-being. We understand and believe in the importance of working with experienced mental health professionals to treat all mental health disorders. Please watch to the end of this video for resources that will link you to accredited therapists who can help you on your journey towards healing.

Our focus is simple - to identify and create ways to overcome many of the challenges we all encounter in life. While the psychology of living in today's world is intriguing, it can also be scary and puzzling at times. Please share with us in the comment section below, if you have ever experienced similar situations, such as the ones described in our video. We'd love to hear your stories and experiences!

title: NHL 23 Gameplay: Nashville Predators vs Boston Bruins - (Xbox Series X) [4K60FPS]
description:
NHL 23 Gameplay: Nashville Predators vs Boston Bruins - Full Match & Gameplay
_____________________________________________________________________________________________
NHL 23 is an ice hockey simulation video game developed by EA Vancouver and published by EA Sports. It will be the 32nd installment in the NHL video game series and was released for the PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Xbox One and Xbox Series X/S on October 14, 2022.
_____________________________________________________________________________________________
NHL 23 will feature "The Zegras", a variant of the lacrosse-style goal performed by Trevor Zegras and Sonny Milano. A player from behind the net hits the puck up above the crossbar and another player in front of the net hits the puck into the goal.

NHL 23 will also feature "Last Chance Puck Movement", a move that will allow the player to hit the puck with their stick even if they have been hit or tripped. NHL 23 may also feature a first-person mode, as seen from the trailer.

NHL 23's "Deep Dive" unveiled new animations, such as new Hat tricks, National anthem animations, on-ice Projection, a new Overtime win animation, Stanley Cup Playoffs animations, along with many other features. Another round of the "Deep Dive" was announced that EA added a custom league option, where you can play as the Original Six, and have the ability to add a Round robin used in the 2020 Stanley Cup playoffs.

Along with many other requested features, same-gen crossplay will be available.
_____________________________________________________________________________________________

WyndRider is a four-piece #Stoner #Doom band from the mountains of East Tennessee. with their first show played in March of 2022. The debut self-titled album, WyndRider, was recorded in late September of the same year by Danielle Fehr from The Wizard Productions. The recordings are the most raw, natural sounding form of the songs that the band was able to capture in a studio setting, while still emulating the energy of a live performance. Bands such as Black Sabbath, Steppenwolf, and Budgie inspired their take on a continuation of heavy and psychedelic music. The themes of this album are a culmination of subjects such as apocalypse, alien life, the Satanic Panic, and sarcastic dissection of the Christian Church. It portrays a new version of the physical, biting addictiveness that Rock and Roll inspired for another generation.

title: Why We are Leaving the United States FOREVER | Minimalist Travel
description:
My husband and I sold everything we own and are leaving the USA (in our late 40s). We appreciate many things about America and it will always hold a place in our hearts, but we feel it is time to leave. The reasons why we are moving out of the states are many. Our grown children live abroad, and we want the flexibility to spend more time with them.  Living abroad while we world travel as digital nomads is an exciting experience, and as empty nesters, we are excited to begin this new chapter of our lives. Living a minimalist lifestyle gives us the freedom to travel the world, just one of many benefits of minimalism. We‚Äôre talking a naturally aspirated 6.5-litre V12, aided by three electric motors, two of which are mounted on the front axle, the third integrated into the new eight-speed dual-clutch transmission.

title: Elemental | Official Trailer
description:
This Summer, meet the residents of Element City

Watch the new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs #Elemental and see the movie in 3D, only in theaters June 16!

Check out a brand-new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù an all-new original feature film that transports moviegoers to an extraordinary place called Element City, where a host of elements live and work. The trailer showcases each element‚Äîair, earth, water and fire‚Äîand what sets them apart according to Ember, a quick-witted and fiery woman who‚Äôs always stayed close to home in Firetown. In ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù which opens in theaters on June 16, she finally ventures out of her comfort zone to explore this spectacular world born from the imaginations of Pixar‚Äôs filmmakers and specifically crafted for the big-screen experience. Element City is inspired by big cities around the globe and embraces theorized contributions from each elemental community‚Äîfrom giant pine-tree-like buildings and waterfall skyscrapers to a tornado-shaped arena called Cyclone Stadium. 

Joining the previously announced voice cast including Leah Lewis and Mamoudou Athie as Ember and Wade, respectively, are Ronnie del Carmen as Ember‚Äôs soon-to-be retired dad, Bernie; Shila Ommi as Ember‚Äôs love-seeking mom, Cinder; Wendi McLendon-Covey as Wade‚Äôs stormy and Air-Ball-loving boss, Gale; Catherine O‚ÄôHara as Wade‚Äôs welcoming mom, Brook; Mason Wertheimer as Ember‚Äôs admiring earth neighbor, Clod; and Joe Pera as an overgrown city bureaucrat, Fern.
 
Directed by Peter Sohn, produced by Denise Ream, p.g.a., and executive produced by Pete Docter, ‚ÄúElemental‚Äù features a screenplay by John Hoberg & Kat Likkel and Brenda Hsueh with story by Sohn, Hoberg & Likkel and Hsueh. The film‚Äôs original score was composed and conducted by Thomas Newman.
